A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Credit Regulation – Reverse Mortgage Loans – Escrow Accounts
3 FOR the purpose of requiring a lender for a reverse mortgage loan to establish a certain
4 escrow account for the payment of certain eligible homeowner expenses, deduct a
5 certain amount of funds from each loan distribution to a borrower, deposit the
6 deducted funds into the escrow account, and deliver on–time payments from the
7 escrow account to the appropriate collection entity for eligible homeowner expenses;
8 and generally relating to reverse mortgage loans and the payment of eligible
9 homeowner expenses.
